<subSubSection pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID="5F272E50-3880-8ABC-6CED-DC5CFB0F4A7B" authority="Dejean, 1826" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphaeroderus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphaeroderus Dejean, 1826</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphaeroderus</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1826: 14. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lecontei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Sphaeroderus lecontei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1826 designated by Hope (1838: 65). Etymology (original). From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">sphaera</emphasis>
(sphere) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">dere</emphasis>
(neck, by extension pronotum), alluding to the round or oval shape of the pronota (&quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">corselet</emphasis>
... 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
arrondi, ovale ou 
<normalizedToken originalValue="orbiculé">orbicule</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
&quot;) of the species then known to Dejean [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Six species restricted to the boreal and temperate regions of eastern North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="152" pageNumber="153" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="152" pageNumber="153">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lindroth’s">Lindroth's</normalizedToken>
(1961a) key covers four of the species currently recognized; 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blatchley" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indianae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Sphaeroderus indianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not included and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schaumii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Sphaeroderus schaumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Sphaeroderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="152" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="152" pageNumber="153">Sphaeroderus nitidicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A taxonomic revision of the genus is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
